    "Above, we used UMAP to visualize MCES distances.",
    "Clearly, any other method for projecting high-dimensional data given as distances (for instance, t-SNE 35, multidimensional scaling 36 or Minimum Spanning Trees) can also be applied (Supplementary Fig. 2) [37] [38] [39].",
